<title>Step 3: Test the Edit</title>

<subheader>(Exercise 7, Add Edits to the Data Entry Application)</subheader>

We are now ready to run the data application and make sure our logic is working properly.

<list ordered>
	<li>Run CSEntry by clicking <image run_button.png /> on the toolbar, or pressing <b>Ctrl+R</b>.</li>
	<li>CSPro will ask you to save the changes. Click <b>Yes</b>.</li>
	<li>CSEntry will ask you to select a data file. Type <b>MyData.dat</b> for the file name, if it is not already there, then press <b>OK</b>.</li>
	<li>Type in any <b>Operator ID</b>.</li>
	<li>Click on <image add_case_button.png /> on the toolbar, or press <b>Ctrl+A</b> to enter <b>Add</b> mode. The first form will appear with the cursor on <b>MyDict identification</b>.</li>
	<li>Type <b>2</b> and then <b>Enter</b> to fill in the ID item. The next form will appear, showing the person roster.</li>
	<li>Type <b>10</b> in the <b>Age</b> field.</li>
	<li>Type <b>1</b> in the <b>Sex</b> field.</li>
	<li>Type <b>1</b> in the <b>Marital status</b> field.</li>
</list>

